======================================================================
  SECTION 8: Monotonicity of w1(beta)
======================================================================

--- Laplace transform monotonicity ---
  w1(beta) = E[exp(-beta*S)] where S = (3 - Re tr U)/3 >= 0
  By standard Laplace transform theory: w1 is STRICTLY DECREASING in beta.
  d/d_beta w1(beta) = E[-S * exp(-beta*S)] < 0  (since S > 0 with positive prob.)
  Consequence: the 1/7 crossing is UNIQUE and the certified sign change
  at [2.079416880123, 2.079416880124] brackets beta_0 exactly.
  MONOTONICITY: VERIFIED (analytic argument, not numerical)

